alexander.puschutil.communication.puem

Class EventBusManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • alexander.puschutil.communication.puem.EventBusManager

  • public class EventBusManager
extends java.lang.Object
    This is the central class of the Event Management system. Events are dispatched to the specific buses here, aswell as callback registering and many more things.

    In order for a method to be suited for callback purposes, it has to be like this:
    callbackMethodName(String sender, SharedResource);
    Naming convention of the EventBuses: ALLCAPS.
    Pre-defined EventBuses:
    -TICK for Regular ticking purposes. Please bear in mind that you have to provide a TickProvider yourself!
    -ERROR for Publishing errors.
    Author:
    Alexander Pusch

      • tick

        public static boolean tick(long tickerKey,
                           java.lang.Object tickContents)
                    throws java.lang.IllegalStateException,
                           InvalidKeyException
        Send a tick event to all TickBus subscribers. Please bear in mind that to be able to tick this, you must be the registered ticker. To become the ticker, see setTicker(MethodWrapper).
        Parameters:
        tickerKey - - the key you get when you requested to be the ticker.
        tickContents - - any information you want to relay when ticking
        Returns:
        If you have the permission to tick this. (AKA your tickerKey is correct and the tick was relayed).
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - - when you call this before initialize()
        InvalidKeyException - - when you provide an invalid key

      • setTicker

        public static long setTicker(MethodWrapper requestTickerChange)
                      throws java.lang.IllegalAccessException,
                             java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                             java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException,
                             java.lang.IllegalStateException
        Call this method if you wish to become the ticker.
        Parameters:
        requestTickerChange - - the wrapper for the method in your class that gets called whenever setTicker() is invoked to ask for permission to change the ticker (This is so to avoid an unauthorized ticker change). This Method must contain no arguments and return a boolean (true for permission, false for denial,)
        Returns:
        The tickerKey that you need in order to call tick() (so don't lose it), if the return value is 0L it means your attempt was denied.

        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - - when construction fails
        java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException - - when construction fails
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - - when you call this before initialize()
